description.narrative: Objectives for Moldova: The Moldova Competitiveness Project (MCP) focuses on leveraging Moldova’s prime tourism assets – wine, gastronomy and rural life – into an engine of economic growth in even the most remote rural regions, contributing to a reduction in poverty and migration. MCP’s tourism strategy provides year-round opportunities, creating a sustainable industry attractive to a range of international markets.

USAID's Competitiveness Project will seek to.promote a strong, diverse, and export-oriented economy by improving.competitiveness and efficiency in key Moldovan industries, creating desirable.well-paying jobs, reducing emigration, and improving the economic well-being of.all Moldovans. The targeted industries include wine production, tourism, light.industry, information technology, creative services and precision engineering..The Project will continue to strengthen industry competitiveness by working.with an estimated 350 Small and Medium Enterprises to improve quality, adopt.new technologies, enhance marketing, and make critical investments in equipment.and people. USAID will continue to grow product quality as the key to preparing.Moldova's private sector to compete in EU and other high-value markets.
